The article discusses the potential benefits of the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, which has passed in both the House and Senate and is now heading to a conference committee. The author argues that the bill would improve the current tax code and lead to a larger economy, resulting in more jobs and higher wages for Americans. The article also highlights specific provisions of the bill, such as lower tax rates for middle-class taxpayers, increased child tax credit, and a cut in the corporate tax rate. The author claims that the bill would stimulate economic growth, encourage businesses to expand and invest, and ultimately benefit American families.